law.text:
In addition to any other powers and duties vested in it by law, the cabinet has the authority, power, and duty to:
Promote the sustainability of Kentucky's forest ecosystems;
Improve, maintain, and protect the health and condition of Kentucky's forest resources;
Promote the most efficient utilization of forest resources;
Provide educational opportunities to increase landowner, logger, and public appreciation, awareness, and knowledge of Kentucky's forests; and
Promulgate administrative regulations under KRS Chapter 13A to accomplish the purposes of KRS 149.330 to 149.355.
